DFProperties.Description:
Placeholder node for the DM-accounts. 
Possible Values:
String; Max Length=49;

Server address. 
Possible Values:
String; Max length=254; Descr=URL;

This value is not used by the client and can be ignored. Furthermore, in some software revisions a software error caused the value "0" to be used instead of the correct value "1" for HTTP. 
Possible Values:
"0"; Descr=A client software error caused the value 0 to be used instead of the correct value '1' for HTTP;
"1"; Descr=HTTP;

Port number to use to connect to server. To "clear" the portnumber, replace with a value of 0 which means "unspecified".
Possible Values: 
Integer; Range=1 to 65535; Descr=Normal port numbers;
0; Descr=No port specified;

This node specifies a server identifier for management server used in the management session. The server id can not be replaced in an existing account. If it needs to be changed, remove the account by deleting the placeholder and subsequently add a new account with the new Server Id. 
Possible Values: 
String; Max length=79;

